# Deny-by-default: ignore everything, then re-include only what `go build` needs.
# Keeps the build context tiny and reproducible (no node_modules, no dist, no
# secrets, no test artifacts). vendor/ is intentionally absent — we `go mod download`.
*

# ── Re-include the Go build inputs ───────────────────────────────────────────
!go.mod
!go.sum
!cmd/
!internal/
!db/

# ── Re-exclude noise that may live under the re-included dirs ─────────────────
**/*_test.go
**/testdata/
**/*.md
**/.DS_Store
